<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FF04FC4BFED0FBBD" bold="true" box="[151,338,1021,1045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">FIGURES 11–16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED16FF94FEC4FC4BFD71FBBD" authority="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[343,755,1021,1045]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FEC4FC4BFE7DFBBD" box="[343,511,1021,1045]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Charippus asper</emphasis>
Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FD6FFC4BFCC9FBBD" bold="true" box="[764,843,1021,1045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED16FF94FD6FFC4BFCC9FBBD" box="[764,843,1021,1045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male (11, 14) and female (12–13, 15 
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FB50FC4BFB52FBBD" bold="true" box="[1219,1232,1021,1045]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">–</emphasis>
16). 11–13. Habitus, in dorsal (11–12) and lateral (13) view, arrow pointing to dense pits on cephalon; 14–15. Front view of carapace; 16. Details of left chelicera, back view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED16FF94FF54FB3DFB3AFAF2" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED16FF94FF54FB3DFB3AFAF2" blockId="4.[151,1437,1163,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FF54FB3DFEC0FB0D" bold="true" box="[199,322,1163,1189]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males morphologically resemble 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED16FF94FD2EFB3DFC33FB0D" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[701,945,1163,1189]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukittimah" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FD2EFB3DFC33FB0D" box="[701,945,1163,1189]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Charippus bukittimah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FC24FB3DFB92FB0D" bold="true" box="[951,1040,1163,1189]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED16FF94FC24FB3DFB92FB0D" box="[951,1040,1163,1189]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the shape of palp, but can be distinguished by the well-developed denticles on the embolic base, two main LEDs distally fused, the rough surface of embolic disc (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FEA0FB65FE0BFB45" box="[307,393,1235,1261]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1113,1137]" captionTargetBox="[294,1294,181,1085]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[282,1306,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Palp of Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (17), ventral (18) and retrolateral (19) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500745/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FE07FB65FE33FB45" box="[404,433,1235,1261]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[272,1311,1200,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-44@5.[272,1316,1198,1948]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Palp of Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (20), ventral (21) and retrolateral (22) view, arrow pointing to the denticles on embolic base." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500749/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">21</figureCitation>
) and by the relatively short RTA (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FCB4FB65FCFFFB45" box="[807,893,1235,1261]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1113,1137]" captionTargetBox="[294,1294,181,1085]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[282,1306,181,1089]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Palp of Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (17), ventral (18) and retrolateral (19) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500745/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FC1BFB65FC2AFB45" box="[904,936,1235,1261]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox="[272,1311,1200,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-44@5.[272,1316,1198,1948]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Palp of Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (20), ventral (21) and retrolateral (22) view, arrow pointing to the denticles on embolic base." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500749/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">22</figureCitation>
); vs. the embolic base lacks denticles and the surface of embolic disc is relatively smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED16FF94FD37FB4EFCBFFAB9" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[676,829,1271,1298]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukittimah" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FD37FB4EFCBFFAB9" box="[676,829,1271,1298]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">C. bukittimah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FCD7FB41FC1CFAB9" bold="true" box="[836,926,1271,1297]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED16FF94FCD7FB41FC1CFAB9" box="[836,926,1271,1297]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. Females can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED16FF94FAA9FB4EFF55FA9D" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukittimah" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FAA9FB4EFF55FA9D" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">C. bukittimah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FF4EFAADFEB4FA9D" bold="true" box="[221,310,1307,1333]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED16FF94FF4EFAADFEB4FA9D" box="[221,310,1307,1333]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the trajectory of copulatory ducts (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FD48FAADFCD8FA9D" box="[731,858,1307,1333]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,181,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[153,1433,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–29. Female genitalia of Charippus asper sp. nov.. 23–25, 27. Ventral view; 26, 28. Dorsal view; 29. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500751/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 23–28</figureCitation>
) and by the ratio of the distance between copulatory ducts to window width (about 2/ 
<quantity id="7273FCBEED16FF94FD97FA89FDAFFAF1" box="[516,557,1343,1369]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED16FF94FDA7FAF6FD11FAF1" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[564,659,1344,1370]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FDA7FAF6FD11FAF1" box="[564,659,1344,1370]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">C. asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FD09FA89FD76FAF1" bold="true" box="[666,756,1343,1369]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED16FF94FD09FA89FD76FAF1" box="[666,756,1343,1369]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
vs. about 1/ 
<quantity id="7273FCBEED16FF94FCE8FA89FC25FAF1" box="[891,935,1343,1369]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED16FF94FC3DFAF6FBC5FAF1" authority="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Wang &amp; Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[942,1095,1343,1370]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bukittimah" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FC3DFAF6FBC5FAF1" box="[942,1095,1343,1370]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">C. bukittimah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FBDDFA89FB25FAF1" bold="true" box="[1102,1191,1343,1369]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED16FF94FBDDFA89FB25FAF1" box="[1102,1191,1343,1369]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED16FF94FF5CFAD5FBEEF815" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED16FF94FF5CFAD5FB4EF96A" blockId="4.[151,1437,1163,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FF5CFAD5FE2EFAD5" bold="true" box="[207,428,1379,1405]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FD33FAD5FD71FAD5" box="[672,755,1379,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1021,1045]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,187,997]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[157,1430,181,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (11, 14) and female (12–13, 15–16). 11–13. Habitus, in dorsal (11–12) and lateral (13) view, arrow pointing to dense pits on cephalon; 14–15. Front view of carapace; 16. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500743/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.21; abdomen length 0.94. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.25, ALE 0.16, PME 0.04, PLE 0.15. Measurements of legs: I 1.87 (0.63, 0.28, 0.44, 0.29, 0.23), II 1.60 (0.53, 0.22, 0.36, 0.26, 0.23), III 1.83 (0.63, 0.21, 0.37, 0.35, 0.27), IV 1.78 (0.58, 0.24, 0.40, 0.34, 0.22). Chelicerae with fang-like projection distally; promargin with two teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Palp (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FF0CFA45FEA1F9A5" box="[159,291,1523,1549]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 17–19" captionStart-1="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId-0="5.[151,264,1113,1137]" captionStartId-1="5.[151,264,1972,1996]" captionTargetBox-0="[294,1294,181,1085]" captionTargetBox-1="[272,1311,1200,1948]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@5.[282,1306,181,1089]" captionTargetId-1="figure-44@5.[272,1316,1198,1948]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 17–19. Palp of Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (17), ventral (18) and retrolateral (19) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 20–22. Palp of Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (20), ventral (21) and retrolateral (22) view, arrow pointing to the denticles on embolic base." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500745" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500749" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500745/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500749/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 17–22</figureCitation>
): embolus coiled for more than a circle, bearing dense denticles at base; embolic disc large and rough, slightly sclerotized, slightly raised centrally; with two main serrulate-edged LED fused distally; tegulum not obviously sclerotized, tegular lobe present; retrolateral tibial apophysis straight, distal part slightly inner-hooked in ventral view; cymbium with retrolateral lamina-like extension. Sternum without setal tuft. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FAFCF9E9FF37F935" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1021,1045]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,187,997]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[157,1430,181,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (11, 14) and female (12–13, 15–16). 11–13. Habitus, in dorsal (11–12) and lateral (13) view, arrow pointing to dense pits on cephalon; 14–15. Front view of carapace; 16. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500743/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
): carapace reddish brown, cephalon slightly darker, dorsal abdomen pale yellow, with dark brown markings, not obviously sclerotized; ventral abdomen grayish brown; legs I–II slightly darker than legs III–IV.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED16FF94FF54F97DFBEEF815" blockId="4.[151,1437,1163,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED16FF94FF54F97DFEA7F94D" bold="true" box="[199,293,1739,1765]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FD83F97DFD0CF94D" box="[528,654,1739,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1021,1045]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,187,997]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[157,1430,181,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (11, 14) and female (12–13, 15–16). 11–13. Habitus, in dorsal (11–12) and lateral (13) view, arrow pointing to dense pits on cephalon; 14–15. Front view of carapace; 16. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500743/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 12, 13</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 1.12; abdomen length 1.11. Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FA98F97DFAD9F94E" box="[1291,1371,1739,1766]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1021,1045]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,187,997]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[157,1430,181,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (11, 14) and female (12–13, 15–16). 11–13. Habitus, in dorsal (11–12) and lateral (13) view, arrow pointing to dense pits on cephalon; 14–15. Front view of carapace; 16. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500743/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) as in males but without fang-like apophysis. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.27, ALE 0.17, PME 0.06, PLE 0.14. Measurements of legs: I 1.52 (0.47, 0.25, 0.36, 0.23, 0.21), II 1.44 (0.46, 0.23, 0.30, 0.24, 0.21), III 1.61 (0.56, 0.19, 0.29, 0.31, 0.26), IV 1.79 (0.55, 0.22, 0.37, 0.35, 0.30). Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FC14F881FB85F8F9" box="[903,1031,1847,1873]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–16" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1021,1045]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,187,997]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[157,1430,181,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 11–16. Charippus asper Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (11, 14) and female (12–13, 15–16). 11–13. Habitus, in dorsal (11–12) and lateral (13) view, arrow pointing to dense pits on cephalon; 14–15. Front view of carapace; 16. Details of left chelicera, back view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500743/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 12–13</figureCitation>
) as in male but slightly lighter. Sternum as in male. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FE46F8EDFD01F8DD" box="[469,643,1883,1910]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,181,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[153,1433,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–29. Female genitalia of Charippus asper sp. nov.. 23–25, 27. Ventral view; 26, 28. Dorsal view; 29. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500751/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 23–25, 27</figureCitation>
): window large, with sclerotized rims, median septum weakly present; lateral depressions small and shallow. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED16FF94FD01F8C9FC91F831" box="[658,787,1919,1945]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–29" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[153,1433,181,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[153,1433,181,1909]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 23–29. Female genitalia of Charippus asper sp. nov.. 23–25, 27. Ventral view; 26, 28. Dorsal view; 29. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500751/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="155">Figs 26, 28</figureCitation>
): CD long and coiled, swerving for eight times; AG small; spermathecae slightly bulging, almost kidney shaped, internally with many protrusions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED16FF94FF54F871FDD2F84A" box="[199,592,1991,2018]" pageId="4" pageNumber="155" type="distribution">
